The Chronicle Bongani Ndlovu, Showbiz Correspondent A member of the globe-trotting Imbube group, Black Umfolosi, Alec Ncube has died. Ncube, a former Sunduza Boys member who joined Black Umfolosi more than 25 years ago, died on Monday  at Mpilo Central Hospital in Bulawayo. He had been battling blood cancer for a year. Sotsha Moyo, one of the group’s founding members confirmed Ncube’s death saying they were devastated. Mourners are gathered at 57472 New Lobengula.